        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 11:11PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 1110 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Aiken Municipal Airport, or 11 miles north of Aiken, moving northeast
at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts to around 40 mph with very heavy rainfall.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Batesburg-Leesville, Saluda, Johnston, Ridge Spring, Saluda County
Airport, Wagener, Pelion, Monetta, Ward, Saluda Co Sheriff's Office,
Thor, Camp Kinard, Emory, Hickory Grove, Hibernia, Steedman, Samaria
Fire Station, Kneece, New Holland, and Cedar Pond Campground.

This includes Interstate 20 in South Carolina between mile markers 24
and 43.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
